# GitHub deploy workflow

When you finish implementing requested code changes in this repo:

1. Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build` locally. Fix failures before continuing.
2. Create a feature branch from latest `main` if not already on one (`feature/short-description` or `fix/short-description`).
3. Commit with a clear message focused on **why**.
4. Push the branch to `origin` — never push directly to `main`.
5. Give the user the PR link: `https://github.com/mcverg1105/homekeeper/pull/new/<branch-name>`
6. Remind them to merge after **lint** and **build** checks pass. Do not merge for them.

## Skip this workflow when

- The user says not to commit or push
- The task was question-only or review-only with no code changes
- Lint or build cannot be fixed in the session — report the blocker instead

## Security

- Never commit `.env` or secrets
- Never force-push `main`

## Shorthand

If the user says **"commit and PR"**, run this full workflow.
